    Use this page to find procedures, job aids and troubleshooting for Compass.

    What is Compass and how does it work?

    You can use Compass to sell and set up products and services suited to your client's unique needs.

    Products and services include:

    • CIBC Employee Share Purchase Loans
    • COPS (when opening or converting an account)
    • Credit cards
    • Creditor insurance products
    • Deposit accounts
    • Employee Purpose Loans
    • Personal chattel loans
    • Real-Estate secured lending (RESL) pre-approvals
    • Switching credit card types
    • Unsecured personal loans
    • Unsecured PLCs (including limit increases)

    For more information, see the Compass Overview page.

    Previous updates
    What's new
    		Details​Resources
    ​Employee Purpose Loans
    • Employee Purpose Loans are set up entirely on Compass
      • Note: When the client's Staff indicator is checked on ECIF, on Compass, select Manage debt > Other reasons from the Primary need drop-down list to see the Employee Purpose Loan.
    • Remote and eSign functions replace manual form, email and secure email document management
    • Loans are automatically disbursed on the Loan Accounting System (LAS) on the disbursement date 
    • ​Employee Borrowing
    • CIBC Purpose Loan Walkthrough
    ​​Employee Share Purchase Loans
    • ​Employee Share Purchase Loans are partially set up on Compass
      • Note: When the client's Staff indicator is checked on ECIF, on Compass, select Borrow Money > Other reasons from the Primary need drop-down list to see the Employee Share Purchase Loan.
    • Client can eSign some forms with a tablet or remotely
    • Loans are automatically disbursed on the Loan Accounting System (LAS) on the disbursement date
    • ​​Employee Share Purchase Loans
    • ESPL Compass Walkthrough

    ​Automated Creditor Insurance Questionnaire
    • ​When a client agrees to apply for a creditor insurance product, they see a Creditor Insurance Questionnaire after the Recommendation screen
      • The questionnaire helps with the insurance discussion, giving clients more details about the product and coverage
      • The client's responses on the questionnaire will help decide whether the client is eligible for insurance coverage
    • Clients must complete a questionnaire for every insurance product they apply for
    • Once the client completes the insurance questionnaire, if they are no longer eligible for the insurance product, they see a notification box telling them to click Remove before continuing
    • Once you go back to the Offer Recommendations screen, you only see the remaining eligible insurance products

    ​myLearning

    • eLearning Module
    • How to: Creditor Insurance Podcast

    Important link

    Complete the Creditor Insurance Questionnaire Screen

    ​Payment Protector offer (for existing credit card clients)
    • ​You'll see CIBC Payment Protector Insurance in the offer recommendations for eligible existing credit card clients
    • Payment Protector Insurance is available on Compass no matter what the client's Needs Purpose is (except for pre-approved Personal Line of Credit [PLC], pre-approved debt consolidation and RRSP express offers)
    • You may be able to select Payment Protector Insurance from the Products, Programs and Offers menu
    		 ​Issue, Cancel or Claim Payment Protector Insurance for Credit Cards
    eSignature (using the Wacom device)
    • If a client has been set up to sign and receive documents electronically, the product origination documents are generated on Compass and displayed on the eSignature device attached to your workstation
    • The advisor and the clients use the eSignature device to review the documents, and then use the stylus to sign and initial the forms
    • Documents are electronically delivered and stored in the client's digital vault
    • Bank copies of eSigned documents are automatically stored and imaged. You can retrieve the documents from Document Search on ECIF
    		 ​myLearning
    • Compass Paperless Origination 
    • Compass Podcast: Printing Forms
    • Compass: Form Simplification Job Aid

    Support materials

    • CPO eSignature Handling Client Objections
    • Signing Device Maintenance
    Digital Vault
    • Clients can view, retrieve and print forms and booklets in their Digital Vault on Online or Mobile Banking by clicking Customer Services. 
    • To access forms and booklets in a PDF format, clients must:
      • Have a CIBC debit card
      • Be registered for Online Banking
      • Download the CIBC Mobile Banking App (if they want to retrieve the documents through Mobile Banking)
    		​myLearning demo
    Online Banking Digital Vault Simulator

    For procedures, see Prepare product forms and get client signature below.

    ​Smart Plus Account
    • ​Clients can link an eligible credit card to their Smart Plus Account
    • Clients will get an automatic fee rebate on one credit card account as long as they meet the eligibility criteria
    • The fee payment option for CIBC Overdraft Protection Service (COPS) defaults to Monthly fixed fee, even if the client is converting from another account that had the pay-per-use option selected

    How do I work a sales case?

    1. Check if there's an existing sales case.
      1. See Search for a Compass Sales Case.
      2. Expand the case list.
      3. Check if there is an open or pending sales case for the product the client is applying for:
        • If yes, resume that sales case
          Note: If there is an existing Online Banking sales case for the client, a message will appear on the Compass landing page. You need to expand the sales case list to review the case before starting a new one. If the open or pending sales case is from Online Banking or Mobile Banking, follow Use Compass to Complete Applications Started on Online or Mobile Banking.
        • If no, start a new one

      Collapse

    2. See the table below for procedures on how to work a Compass sales case. The procedures are listed in the order the screens appear as you work on your case.

    6. Prepare product forms and get client signature

    Note: For unsecured personal loans and lines of credit (non-RESL) products: you must scan the required documents before funding. And as a temporary measure, once the product has been activated or disbursed, you must also send the documents to RCS using the appropriate sleeve.

    		​Print Forms — Signing Preference
